.TH createSpecialDrcRegion  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBcreateSpecialDrcRegion\fR \-  DRC region layers define a special masterslice layer that is used to define the areas of a region on which a set of rules defined in the metal, cut, and/or trim metal layers with the REGION property would be applied. The createSpecialDrcRegion command can be used to add drc region blockages in or around the die area except specified macros
.SH Syntax \fBcreateSpecialDrcRegion\fR  [-help]   [-extendOuterX <float>]  [-extendOuterY <float>]   [-extendX <float>]  [-extendY <float>]   [-insts <string>]  -layer <string>
.P DRC region layers define a special masterslice layer that is used to define the areas of a region on which a set of rules defined in the metal, cut, and/or trim metal layers with the REGION property would be applied. The createSpecialDrcRegion command can be used to add drc region blockages in or around the die area except specified macros. 
.SH Parameters   "\fB-extendOuterX <float>  \fR" Expands the routing blockage in X direction.   Data_type: float, optional  "\fB-extendOuterY <float>  \fR" Expands the routing blockage in Y direction.   Data_type: float, optional   "\fB-extendX <float>  \fR" Expands the non-routing blockage in X direction.  Data_type: float, optional   "\fB-extendY <float>  \fR" Expands the non-routing blockage in X direction.  Data_type: float, optional   "\fB-help\fR" Outputs a brief description that includes the type and default information for each createSpecialDrcRegion parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command:   man createSpecialDrcRegion  "\fB-insts <string>  \fR" Specifies the name of the hierarchical instance that are to be cut out.  Note: Wild card characters are not supported while specifying hierarchical instance names.  Note: All blocks are included if -insts is not specified or when -insts{} is specified.  Data_type: string, optional  "\fB-layer <string>  \fR" Specifies the names of the layers on which the routing blockage is created.  Data_type: string, optional 
.SH Example
.RS  "*" 2 The following command creates a routing blockage on R1 that blocks out DTMF_INST/PLLCLK_INST:  createSpecialDrcRegion -layer R1 -extendOutterX 10 -extendOutterY 20 -insts DTMF_INST/PLLCLK_INST  (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.)   "*" 2 The following command creates a routing blockage on R1 that blocks out DTMF_INST/RAM_256x16_TEST_INST/RAM_256x16_INST:  createSpecialDrcRegion -layer R1 -extendX 10 -extendY 20 -insts DTMF_INST/RAM_256x16_TEST_INST/RAM_256x16_INST  (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.) 
.RE 
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide
.RE
.P
